public class Database {
    /*

Sellers Table:

Columns/Attributes:
sellerID (Primary Key): A unique identifier for each seller.
nickname: The seller's chosen nickname.
balance: The seller's account balance (BITScoin balance).
products: A list of products listed by the seller.
Each product should have attributes such as productName, description, askingPrice, expiryTime, and a unique product ID.
Buyers Table:

Columns/Attributes:
buyerID (Primary Key): A unique identifier for each buyer.
nickname: The buyer's chosen nickname.
balance: The buyer's account balance (BITScoin balance).
Products Table:

Columns/Attributes:
productID (Primary Key): A unique identifier for each product.
sellerID: The ID of the seller who listed the product.
productName: The name of the product.
description: A description of the product.
askingPrice: The price set by the seller.
expiryTime: The date and time when the product listing expires.
You may include additional product-specific attributes as needed.
Bids Table:

Columns/Attributes:
bidID (Primary Key): A unique identifier for each bid.
buyerID: The ID of the buyer who placed the bid.
productID: The ID of the product the bid is placed on.
bidAmount: The amount of the bid.
timestamp: The date and time when the bid was placed.
You may include additional bid-specific attributes as needed.
Messages Table:

Columns/Attributes:
messageID (Primary Key): A unique identifier for each message.
senderID: The ID of the user (either buyer or seller) who sent the message.
receiverID: The ID of the user (either buyer or seller) who received the message.
content: The content of the message.
timestamp: The date and time when the message was sent.
     */
}
